3.1 log @A note about minor edits @ text @<?xml version='1.1' encoding='UTF-8'?> <xwikidoc version="1.3" reference="Help.History.WebHome" locale=""> <web>Help.History</web> <name>WebHome</name> <language/> <defaultLanguage>en</defaultLanguage> <translation>0</translation> <creator>XWiki.Admin</creator> <creationDate>1487065944000</creationDate> <parent>Main.WebHome</parent> <author>XWiki.Admin</author> <contentAuthor>XWiki.Admin</contentAuthor> <date>1487067065000</date> <contentUpdateDate>1487067065000</contentUpdateDate> <version>3.1</version> <title/> <comment>A note about minor edits</comment> <minorEdit>false</minorEdit> <syntaxId>xwiki/2.1</syntaxId> <hidden>false</hidden> <content>Any change made to a document is saved under Version Control. You can see the version of a document by looking at "**History**" tab the bottom of the document.&#xd; &#xd; A document version is identifier by two numbers, separated by a dot: &lt;Major>.&lt;Minor> (e.g. 3.2). The XWiki versioning system allows the distinction between major and minor edits. When editing a page, the user has the option to decide whether his edit brings major or minor changes to the document. Saving a major version will increase the first component and reset the second to "1", while a minor version will just increase the second component.&#xd; &#xd; By default, minor edits do not appear in the document history. The option "Show minor edits" will list all the versions, including minor ones.</content> </xwikidoc>@
